children.desc: returns the base-`E` logarithm of `z`. `Ln(z)` will be converted to `Log(z)` in symbolic mode.

children.name: Log10.md
children.desc: returns the base-`10` logarithm of `z`. `Log10(z)` will be converted to `Log(z)/Log(10)` in symbolic mode.

children.name: Log2.md
children.desc: returns the base-`2` logarithm of `z`. `Log2(z)` will be converted to `Log(z)/Log(2)` in symbolic mode.

children.name: LogisticSigmoid.md
children.desc: returns the logistic sigmoid of `z`.

children.name: LogNormalDistribution.md
children.desc: returns a log-normal distribution.

children.name: LucasL.md
children.desc: gives the `n`th Lucas number.

children.name: LUDecomposition.md
children.desc: calculate the LUP-decomposition of a square `matrix`.

children.name: MachineNumberQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `expr` is a machine-precision real or complex number.

children.name: MangoldtLambda.md
children.desc: the von Mangoldt function of `n`

children.name: ManhattanDistance.md
children.desc: returns the Manhattan distance between `u` and `v`, which is the number of horizontal or vertical moves in the grid like Manhattan city layout to get from `u` to `v`.

children.name: MatchingDissimilarity.md
children.desc: returns the Matching dissimilarity between the two boolean 1-D lists `u` and `v`, which is defined as `(c_tf + c_ft) / n`, where `n` is `len(u)` and `c_ij` is the number of occurrences of `u(k)=i` and `v(k)=j` for `k<n`.

children.name: MatchQ.md
children.desc: tests whether `expr` matches `form`.

children.name: MathMLForm.md
children.desc: returns the MathMLForm form of the evaluated `expr`.

children.name: MatrixMinimalPolynomial.md
children.desc: computes the matrix minimal polynomial of a `matrix` for the variable `var`.

children.name: MatrixPower.md
children.desc: computes the `n`th power of a `matrix`

children.name: MatrixRank.md
children.desc: returns the rank of `matrix`.

children.name: Max.md
children.desc: returns the expression with the greatest value among the `e_i`.

children.name: Maximize.md
children.desc: returns the maximum of the unary function for the given `variable`.

children.name: MemberQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if pattern matches any element of `list`, or `False` otherwise.

children.name: MersennePrimeExponent.md
children.desc: returns the  `n`th mersenne prime exponent. `2^n - 1` must be a prime number.

children.name: MersennePrimeExponentQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `2^n - 1` is a prime number. Currently `0 <= n <= 45` can be computed in reasonable time.

children.name: Message.md
children.desc: displays the specified message, replacing placeholders in the message text with the corresponding expressions.

children.name: MessageName.md
children.desc: `symbol::msg` identifies a message. `MessageName` is the head of message IDs of the form `symbol::tag`.

children.name: Min.md
children.desc: returns the expression with the lowest value among the `e_i`.

children.name: Minimize.md
children.desc: returns the minimum of the unary function for the given `variable`.

children.name: Minus.md
children.desc: is the negation of `expr`.

children.name: MissingQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `expr` is a `Missing()` expression.

children.name: Mod.md
children.desc: returns `x` modulo `m`.

children.name: Module.md
children.desc: evaluates `expr` for the `list_of_local_variables` by renaming local variables.

children.name: MoebiusMu.md
children.desc: calculate the MÃ¶bius function.

children.name: MonomialList.md
children.desc: get the list of monomials of a `polynomial` expression, with respect to the `list-of-variables`.

children.name: Most.md
children.desc: returns `expr` with the last element removed.

children.name: Multinomial.md
children.desc: gives the multinomial coefficient `(n1+n2+â€¦)!/(n1! n2! â€¦)`.

children.name: MultiplicativeOrder.md
children.desc: gives the multiplicative order `a` modulo `n`.

children.name: NakagamiDistribution.md
children.desc: returns a Nakagami distribution.

children.name: Nand.md
children.desc: Logical NAND function. It evaluates its arguments in order, giving `True` immediately if any of them are `False`, and `False` if they are all `True`.

children.name: Negative.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` is a negative real number.

children.name: Nest.md
children.desc: starting with `expr`, iteratively applies `f` `n` times and returns the final result.

children.name: NestList.md
children.desc: starting with `expr`, iteratively applies `f` `n` times and returns a list of all intermediate results.

children.name: NHoldAll.md
children.desc: is an attribute that protects all arguments of a function from numeric evaluation.

children.name: NIntegrate.md
children.desc: computes the numerical univariate real integral of `f` with respect to `x` from `a` to `b`.

children.name: NMaximize.md
children.desc: the `NMaximize` function provides an implementation of [George Dantzig's simplex algorithm](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simplex_algorithm) for solving linear optimization problems with linear equality and inequality constraints and implicit non-negative variables.

children.name: NMinimize.md
children.desc: the `NMinimize` function provides an implementation of [George Dantzig's simplex algorithm](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simplex_algorithm) for solving linear optimization problems with linear equality and inequality constraints and implicit non-negative variables.

children.name: NonNegative.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` is a positive real number or zero.

children.name: NonPositive.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` is a negative real number or zero.

children.name: Nor.md
children.desc: Logical NOR function. It evaluates its arguments in order, giving `False` immediately if any of them are `True`, and `True` if they are all `False`.

children.name: Normal.md
children.desc: converts a special Symja expression `expr` into a standard expression.

children.name: Not.md
children.desc: negates the logical expression `expr`.

children.name: NRoots.md
children.desc: gives the numerical roots of polynomial `poly`.

children.name: Null.md
children.desc: is the implicit result of expressions that do not yield a result.

children.name: NullSpace.md
children.desc: returns a list of vectors that span the nullspace of the `matrix`.

children.name: NumberQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `expr` is an explicit number, and `False` otherwise.

children.name: Numerator.md
children.desc: gives the numerator in `expr`.

children.name: NumericQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `expr` is an explicit numeric expression, and `False` otherwise.

children.name: OddQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` is odd, and `False` otherwise.

children.name: OneIdentity.md
children.desc: is an attribute specifying that `f(x)` should be treated as equivalent to `x` in pattern matching.

children.name: OptimizeExpression.md
children.desc: common subexpressions elimination for a complicated `function` by generating "dummy" variables for these subexpressions.

children.name: Optional.md
children.desc: is a pattern which matches `patt`, which if omitted should be replaced by `default`.

children.name: Or.md
children.desc: `expr1 || expr2 || â€¦` evaluates each expression in turn, returning `True` as soon as an expression evaluates to `True`. If all expressions evaluate to `False`, `Or` returns `False`.

children.name: Order.md
children.desc: is `0` if `a` equals `b`. Is `-1` or `1` according to canonical order of `a` and `b`.

children.name: OrderedQ.md
children.desc: is `True` if `a` sorts before `b` according to canonical ordering.

children.name: Orthogonalize.md
children.desc: returns a basis for the orthogonalized set of vectors defined by `matrix`.

children.name: Outer.md
children.desc: computes a generalised outer product of `x` and `y`, using the function `f` in place of multiplication.

children.name: Part.md
children.desc: returns part `i` of `expr`.

children.name: PartitionsP.md
children.desc: gives the number of unrestricted partitions of the integer `n`.

children.name: PartitionsQ.md
children.desc: gives the number of partitions of the integer `n` into distinct parts

children.name: PatternTest.md
children.desc: constrains `pattern` to match `expr` only if the evaluation of `test(expr)` yields `True`.

children.name: PerfectNumber.md
children.desc: returns the `n`th perfect number. In number theory, a perfect number is a positive integer that is equal to the sum of its proper

children.name: PerfectNumberQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `n` is a perfect number. In number theory, a perfect number is a positive integer that is equal to the sum of its proper

children.name: Pi.md
children.desc: is the constant `Pi`.

children.name: Pochhammer.md
children.desc: returns the pochhammer symbol for a rational number `a` and an integer number `n`.

children.name: PoissonDistribution.md
children.desc: returns a Poisson distribution.

children.name: PolynomialQ.md
children.desc: return `True` if `p` is a polynomial for the variable `x`. Return `False` in all other cases.

children.name: Positive.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` is a positive real number.

children.name: PossibleZeroQ.md
children.desc: maps a (possible) zero `expr` to `True` and returns `False` otherwise.

children.name: PowerExpand.md
children.desc: expands out powers of the form `(x^y)^z` and `(x*y)^z` in `expr`.

children.name: PowerMod.md
children.desc: computes `x^y` modulo `m`.

children.name: PreDecrement.md
children.desc: decrements `x` by `1`, returning the new value of `x`.

children.name: PreIncrement.md
children.desc: increments `x` by `1`, returning the new value of `x`.

children.name: Prepend.md
children.desc: returns `expr` with `item` prepended to its leaves.

children.name: PrependTo.md
children.desc: prepend `item` to value of `s` and sets `s` to the result.

children.name: Prime.md
children.desc: returns the `n`th prime number.

children.name: PrimeOmega.md
children.desc: returns the sum of the exponents of the prime factorization of `n`.

children.name: PrimePi.md
children.desc: gives the number of primes less than or equal to `x`.

children.name: PrimePowerQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `n` is a power of a prime number.

children.name: PrimitiveRootList.md
children.desc: returns the list of the primitive roots of `n`.

children.name: Probability.md
children.desc: returns the probability of the `pure-function` for the given `data-set`.

children.name: ProductLog.md
children.desc: returns the value of the Lambert W function at `z`.

children.name: PseudoInverse.md
children.desc: computes the Moore-Penrose pseudoinverse of the `matrix`. If `matrix` is invertible, the pseudoinverse equals the inverse.

children.name: QRDecomposition.md
children.desc: computes the QR decomposition of the `matrix`.

children.name: Quantity.md
children.desc: returns the quantity for `value` and `unit`

children.name: QuantityMagnitude.md
children.desc: returns the value of the `quantity`

children.name: Quotient.md
children.desc: computes the integer quotient of `m` and `n`.

children.name: QuotientRemainder.md
children.desc: computes a list of the quotient and remainder from division of `m` and `n`.

children.name: RandomChoice.md
children.desc: chooses a random `arg` from the list.

children.name: RandomInteger.md
children.desc: create a random integer number between `0` and `n`.

children.name: RandomPrime.md
children.desc: create a random prime integer number between `2` and `n`.

children.name: RandomReal.md
children.desc: create a random number between `0.0` and `1.0`.

children.name: Rationalize.md
children.desc: convert numerical real or imaginary parts in (sub-)expressions into rational numbers.

children.name: Re.md
children.desc: returns the real component of the complex number `z`.

children.name: Real.md
children.desc: is the head of real (inexact) numbers.

children.name: RealNumberQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `expr` is an explicit number with no imaginary component.

children.name: Reals.md
children.desc: is the set of real numbers.

children.name: Reap.md
children.desc: gives the result of evaluating `expr`, together with all values sown during this evaluation. Values sown with different tags are given in different lists.

children.name: Refine.md
children.desc: evaluate the `expression` for the given `assumptions`.

children.name: Rest.md
children.desc: returns `expr` with the first element removed.

children.name: Resultant.md
children.desc: computes the resultant of the polynomials `polynomial1` and `polynomial2` with respect to the variable `var`.

children.name: Reverse.md
children.desc: reverse the elements of the `list`.

children.name: Riffle.md
children.desc: insert elements of `list2` between the elements of `list1`.

children.name: RogersTanimotoDissimilarity.md
children.desc: returns the Rogers-Tanimoto dissimilarity between the two boolean 1-D lists `u` and `v`, which is defined as `R / (c_tt + c_ff + R)` where n is `len(u)`, `c_ij` is the number of occurrences of `u(k)=i` and `v(k)=j` for `k<n`, and `R = 2 * (c_tf + c_ft)`.

children.name: Roots.md
children.desc: determine the roots of a univariate polynomial equation with respect to the variable `var`.

children.name: Round.md
children.desc: round a given `expr` to nearest integer.

children.name: RowReduce.md
children.desc: returns the reduced row-echelon form of `matrix`.

children.name: RussellRaoDissimilarity.md
children.desc: returns the Russell-Rao dissimilarity between the two boolean 1-D lists `u` and `v`, which is defined as `(n - c_tt) / c_tt` where `n` is `len(u)` and `c_ij` is the number of occurrences of `u(k)=i` and `v(k)=j` for `k<n`.

children.name: SameQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` and `y` are structurally identical.

children.name: SatisfiableQ.md
children.desc: test whether the `boolean-expr` is satisfiable by a combination of boolean `False` and `True` values for the `list-of-variables`.

children.name: Sec.md
children.desc: returns the secant of `z`.

children.name: Sech.md
children.desc: returns the hyperbolic secant of `z`.

children.name: Select.md
children.desc: returns a list of the elements `ei` for which `f(ei)` returns `True`.

children.name: Series.md
children.desc: create a power series of `expr` up to order `(x- x0)^n` at the point `x = x0`

children.name: SeriesCoefficient.md
children.desc: get the coefficient of `(x- x0)^n` at the point `x = x0`

children.name: SeriesData.md
children.desc: internal structure of a power series at the point `x = x0` the `coeff`-i are coefficients of the power series.

children.name: SetAttributes.md
children.desc: adds `attrib` to `symbol`'s attributes.

children.name: SetDelayed.md
children.desc: assigns `value` to `expr`, without evaluating `value`.

children.name: Sign.md
children.desc: gives `-1`, `0` or `1` depending on whether `x` is negative, zero or positive.

children.name: Sin.md
children.desc: the sine function.

children.name: Sinc.md
children.desc: the sinc function `Sin(expr)/expr` for `expr != 0`. `Sinc(0)` returns `1`.

children.name: SingularValueDecomposition.md
children.desc: calculates the singular value decomposition for the `matrix`.

children.name: Sinh.md
children.desc: returns the hyperbolic sine of `z`.

children.name: Skewness.md
children.desc: gives Pearson's moment coefficient of skewness for `list` (a measure for estimating the symmetry of a distribution).

children.name: SokalSneathDissimilarity.md
children.desc: returns the Sokal-Sneath dissimilarity between the two boolean 1-D lists `u` and `v`, which is defined as `R / (c_tt + R)` where n is `len(u)`, `c_ij` is the number of occurrences of `u(k)=i` and `v(k)=j` for `k<n`, and `R = 2 * (c_tf + c_ft)`.

children.name: Sow.md
children.desc: sends the value `expr` to the innermost `Reap`.

children.name: Span.md
children.desc: is the head of span ranges like `1;;3`.

children.name: SplitBy.md
children.desc: splits `list` into collections of consecutive elements that give the same result when `f` is applied.

children.name: Sqrt.md
children.desc: returns the square root of `expr`.

children.name: SquaredEuclideanDistance.md
children.desc: returns squared the euclidean distance between `u$` and `v`.

children.name: SquareFreeQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `n` a square free integer number or a square free univariate polynomial.

children.name: SquareMatrixQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `m` is a square matrix.

children.name: StirlingS1.md
children.desc: returns the Stirling numbers of the first kind.

children.name: StirlingS2.md
children.desc: returns the Stirling numbers of the second kind. `StirlingS2(n,k)` is the number of ways of partitioning an `n`-element set into `k` non-empty subsets.

children.name: StruveH.md
children.desc: returns the Struve function `H_n(z)`.

children.name: StruveL.md
children.desc: returns the modified Struve function `L_n(z)`.

children.name: StudentTDistribution.md
children.desc: returns a Student's t-distribution.

children.name: Subfactorial.md
children.desc: returns the subfactorial number of the integer `n`

children.name: Subtract.md
children.desc: represents the subtraction of `b` from `a`.

children.name: SubtractFrom.md
children.desc: is equivalent to `x = x - dx`.

children.name: Surd.md
children.desc: returns the `n`-th root of `expr`. If the result is defined, it's a real value.

children.name: Switch.md
children.desc: yields the first `value` for which `expr` matches the corresponding pattern.

children.name: Symbol.md
children.desc: is the head of symbols.

children.name: SymbolName.md
children.desc: returns the name of the symbol `s` (without any leading context name).

children.name: SymbolQ.md
children.desc: is `True` if `x` is a symbol, or `False` otherwise.

children.name: SymmetricMatrixQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `m` is a symmetric matrix.

children.name: SyntaxQ.md
children.desc: is `True` if the given `str` is a string which has the correct syntax.

children.name: Take.md
children.desc: returns `expr` with all but the first `n` leaves removed.

children.name: Tan.md
children.desc: the tangent function.

children.name: Tanh.md
children.desc: returns the hyperbolic tangent of `z`.

children.name: TautologyQ.md
children.desc: test whether the `boolean-expr` is satisfiable by all combinations of boolean `False` and `True` values for the `list-of-variables`.

children.name: TeXForm.md
children.desc: returns the TeX form of the evaluated `expr`.

children.name: Through.md
children.desc: gives `p(f(x))`.

children.name: TimesBy.md
children.desc: is equivalent to `x = x * dx`.

children.name: TimeValue.md
children.desc: returns an time value calculation.

children.name: Timing.md
children.desc: returns a list with the first entry containing the evaluation time of `x` and the second entry is the evaluation result of `x`.

children.name: ToCharacterCode.md
children.desc: converts `string` into a list of corresponding integer numbers.

children.name: Together.md
children.desc: writes sums of fractions in `expr` together.

children.name: ToString.md
children.desc: converts `expr` into a string.

children.name: Tr.md
children.desc: computes the trace of the `matrix`.

children.name: Trace.md
children.desc: return the evaluation steps which are used to get the result.

children.name: TrigExpand.md
children.desc: expands out trigonometric expressions in `expr`.

children.name: TrigReduce.md
children.desc: rewrites products and powers of trigonometric functions in `expr` in terms of trigonometric functions with combined arguments.

children.name: TrigToExp.md
children.desc: converts trigonometric functions in `expr` to exponentials.

children.name: TrueQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if and only if `expr` is `True`.

children.name: Union.md
children.desc: get the union set from `set1` and `set2`.

children.name: Unitize.md
children.desc: maps a non-zero `expr` to `1`, and a zero `expr` to `0`.

children.name: UnitStep.md
children.desc: returns `0`, if `expr` is less than `0` and returns `1`, if `expr` is greater equal than `0`.

children.name: UnsameQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if `x` and `y` are not structurally identical.

children.name: Unset.md
children.desc: removes any definitions belonging to the left-hand-side `expr`.

children.name: UpperCaseQ.md
children.desc: is `True` if the given `str` is a string which only contains upper case characters.

children.name: ValueQ.md
children.desc: returns `True` if and only if `expr` is defined.

children.name: VandermondeMatrix.md
children.desc: gives the Vandermonde matrix with `n` rows and columns.

children.name: Variables.md
children.desc: gives a list of the variables that appear in the polynomial `expr`.

children.name: VectorAngle.md
children.desc: gives the angles between vectors `u` and `v`

children.name: WeibullDistribution.md
children.desc: returns a Weibull distribution.

children.name: With.md
children.desc: evaluates `expr` for the `list_of_local_variables` by replacing the local variables in `expr`.

children.name: Xor.md
children.desc: Logical XOR (exclusive OR) function. Returns `True` if an odd number of the arguments are `True` and the rest are `False`. Returns `False` if an even number of the arguments are `True` and the rest are `False`.

children.name: YuleDissimilarity.md
children.desc: returns the Yule dissimilarity between the two boolean 1-D lists `u` and `v`, which is defined as R / (c_tt * c_ff + R / 2) where n is `len(u)`, `c_ij` is the number of occurrences of `u(k)=i` and `v(k)=j` for `k<n`, and `R = 2 * c_tf * c_ft`.

children.name: Zeta.md
children.desc: returns the Riemann zeta function of `z`.
